The paper deals with index coding problems in wireless communication networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves linear algebraic techniques for constructing optimal index codes, which are relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the decoding complexity of the proposed index codes, which is related to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
